After a moment of hesitation, I steady my breathing carefully, raise my left hand, reach for the backpack and slowly unzip it. Just as I'm about to grab the phone, I lose my balance, sliding quickly downward, I forced my arms and legs against the cliff and narrowly saved myself. Now I have nowhere to go. Above me, soft sand, below, high rocks. One wrong move and I'm dead for sure. Fear and helplessness spread through my body. Suddenly, an idea hits me. I begin to calculate the intervals between waves hitting the rocks. After a few checks, I find the right moment. I Turn around. I don't die from the fall, but the water is too shallow. My weight slams into a rock. Pain surges through me and I lose consciousness. Luckily, I regain awareness, quickly swim back to the surface and climb up the nearest rock. I've made it just barely. I'm overjoyed. My tense nerve is finally relaxing. But then I feel a sharp pain in my palm and realize my hand has been cut with a 10 centimeter long gash. It's a shocking sight, too gruesome to look at, but at least I'm still alive. After studying myself, I prepare to leave. But the moment I take a step, I crash hard onto the rocks and pass out. I don't know how long it's been, but the waves wake me. I try to move, but my legs are paralyzed. During the fall, my pelvis was crushed by the rocks and I'm slowly losing feeling in my feet. Then I remember my phone, but it's been ruined by the seawater, totally useless. I look helplessly at the sky calling out, but in this deserted sea, there's no response. I take off my shirt, bandage the wound and look around, searching for a way out. In the distance, an island is my only hope. I decide to take a chance, grab my bag and struggle toward the rocks. One quick roll, I dive back into the sea, dragging my half paralyzed body, using one arm to swim with all my might. Halfway There I feel a sharp pain in my abdomen, and suddenly I disappear below the surface. I instinctively scream, but my voice is lost in bubbles. Survival instincts keep me fighting, and finally, I break the surface again, but I'm exhausted, and the lack of oxygen knocks me out. This time, I have no strength left to fight. My body sinks slowly. My feet touch the seafloor.

Outside the train, the temperature drops to minus 100 degrees Celsius. After a few seconds, the pain gave way to numbness. The man's hands became increasingly rigid from the cold. The man screams echoed throughout the entire train, yet no one dared to resist. This was a world of extreme cold, where humanity could only survive on this train. The train had been running continuously for 17 years, without ever stopping. The rich lived in the front cars, wielding all the power and enjoying a luxurious life. They drank the finest wine, held parties, and used various entertainment facilities. Their lives always rich and colorful. Meanwhile, in the rear cars of the train, the poor were packed together like livestock. Population was large, but their lives were extremely miserable. Their food consisted of the rich people's scraps, a ration called a protein bar. They had survived on this food for 17 years. Every month, the rich would select children from the poor to take away. Anyone who resisted was met with violence, suppression, As demonstrated by the man at the beginning, it wasn't until one day that someone secretly discovered that these protein bars were actually made from dead cockroaches. The poor had never known what they were truly eating due to years of pent up resentment. The leader of the tail section, Captain America. He was determined to overthrow the rich. To start the revolt, he collected a pile of iron barrels. On this day, the soldiers came to deliver food. Again. They opened the iron door. The captain felt the time was right. With a determination to die, he rushed toward the soldiers. He grabbed a soldier's gun. He had guessed correctly. The soldier's gun was empty. Instantly, the entire lower class population rioted. They pushed the iron barrels forward to jam the iron door. This was the first step of their resistance.

He dragged me to the parking lot and shoved me into his car. What surprised me was, though he'd stolen my car, he couldn't drive a manual transmission. Watching him panic, I suddenly found him intriguing. In the end, he had to ask me to drive, but barely a few blocks in, the man needed to pee. He threatened me to wait in the car while he hurried off. Even while using the restroom, he kept glancing back to see if I'd escape, but escape never crossed my mind. I wanted to see what he was up to. What surprised me was that upon returning to the car, he started apologizing. His name was Billy. Five years ago, he'd been framed and sent to prison. Today was his release day. He wanted me to pretend to be his wife and accompany him home to visit his parents. Then he planned to kill the enemy who framed him for prison. If I helped him fulfill this wish, he'd let me go. Seeing this beautiful man before me, I had no choice but to agree to his request. But as soon as We arrived home. He didn't even dare knock on the door. He started the entrance with his head bowed, overcome with fear. After my patient persuasion, he finally stepped forward to knock. His father opened the door, yet his face showed no trace of joy. Inside, father and son exchanged not a word. His mother, however, seemed quite pleased with me as her fake daughter in law. I told his parents that Billy was a good man, that I felt fortunate to marry him. Though I spoke sincerely, Billy's father merely nodded perfunctorily. His mother, meanwhile, was completely absorbed in the television. Clearly, they couldn't care less about Billy. Even when the football match ended in defeat, his mother took her frustration out on Billy. God damn it, 30 years I haven't missed a game. voice_to_text: At Grandpa's funeral, Jack secretly slipped his phone into the coffin because it was Grandpa's favorite thing. After Grandpa was buried, Jack missed him terribly, so he sent a text message to Grandpa's phone. He put his phone down. Suddenly lightning flashed and thunder roared outside. The next morning, Jack discovered he'd actually received a reply. Text from Grandpa contained a strange coded message. Jack was terrified. He rushed downstairs to tell his father, saying Grandpa wasn't really dead. But his father didn't believe him at all. So Jack showed him the text message. His father explained this was probably just a signal glitch. And besides, the coroner had confirmed Grandpa definitely died of a heart attack. But Jack still didn't buy it because the coded message was their secret distress signal. So Jack rushed to the cemetery, pulled out his phone and dialed Grandpa's number. Then he pressed his ear to the ground and listened carefully. Sure enough, could actually hear a phone ringing underground. This meant the phone hadn't been taken by anyone. Jack instantly panicked. He couldn't understand what was going on. Was Grandpa still alive? Later, he went to Grandpa's house, trying to find some clues, but he didn't find anything unusual. A month later, Jack gradually emerged from his grief. The Christmas party that night, Jack simply asked the popular girl to dance, but his classmate got jealous. He got beaten up pretty badly. Afraid of more revenge from his classmate, Jack didn't dare tell His father about it. He secretly hid in the bathroom and called Grandpa's voicemail telling Grandpa what happened. However, the next day, his classmate told him the boy who bullied him yesterday was dead. Jack couldn't believe it. He went to the scene and saw the boy's body being carried away by police. Coroner told Jack the deceased boy was positioned in a weird pose with his arms crossed, which was exactly how Jack had been pinned down yesterday. Jack felt this incident was connected to Grandpa. That night, he called Grandpa again, sharing his inner confusion. But as soon as he hung up, Grandpa actually called him back.

Too beaten to stand up, all she wanted to do was crawl to the living room as quickly as possible. She just hoped that the camera on the cupboard could capture everything clearly. Sure enough, the next moment her husband dragged her back into the room. And with a loud scream, the husband's anger had finally been vented. But as Lisa was silently cleaning up the mess, she cut her finger on a broken glass. But this time her husband didn't scold her. Instead, he took out a present from his bag and threw it in front of Lisa. Lisa was very confused, but the next moment the husband asked his wife what kind of fruit she wanted. When Lisa remained silent, the husband became impatient again. And then he said that Lisa was already five months pregnant. If it were any other woman, she would have wanted fruit. When he heard that the woman wanted strawberries, the man immediately took out a bank note and handed it to his wife so that she could buy them herself. But the man did not know that his wife not only did not buy strawberries, instead she bought a bucket of ice cream, which pregnant women are not allowed to eat. Then he found a deserted place to sit alone. Until late at night, when she was sure her husband was asleep, she went to the toilet and ate it in secret. And when she was done, she tiptoed around and took pictures of her bruises. Then she would send them to her colleagues, asking if they could be used as evidence for divorce. The next day, the woman came to work, but before the end of the day, she received a phone call from her husband urging her to leave. Lisa had to leave early, but when she reached the stairwell, she suddenly removed the pillow from her waist. Then she switched her mobile phone to record mode and got into the car. Lisa remained silent in the face of the reprimand. Then she secretly put her mobile phone next to her. However, when the car had just traveled a short distance, just because she sneezed, her husband started to abuse her again. He almost crashed into the car in front of her. But the next moment, the husband realized that his pregnant wife's first reaction to danger was not to protect her stomach. While the husband was scolding his wife again, Lisa noticed something strange about the navigation, because today they said they were going to go back to her mother's house with her, but the address that her husband was navigating to was not. At this point, the husband changed the subject. He asked Lisa to guess how much cash she could put in the bag in The back seat. Without waiting for Lisa's answer, he said that the baby was on the way. Shouldn't they have a better life together? By nightfall, her husband had driven the car into a tunnel with Lisa. But when the clock pointed to 1:00, Lisa went back to her mother's house alone. She took off all her clothes and washed them. Then she sat in the bathtub and washed herself. Only when she was done did she lay down beside her mother in a state of restlessness. The next morning, Lisa packed her things and was ready to leave. But while she was waiting for the lift, a mysterious phone call told Lisa that her husband was dead. Meanwhile, in a villa, a woman who had just moved here three months ago was staring at the yard because she felt a bad odor in the yard that she couldn't describe. But just as she was about to take a shovel to find out what was going on. But when her husband and son came back, they told her it was the smell of the garden's nutrients. But that day, when the neighbors asked her about the stench in the yard, Anna explained that it was the smell of manure. This world. I created it. But today, I suddenly found everything around me incredibly noisy. It turned out that humans were experimenting with friction to make fire. Watching this, I found it somewhat amusing because it would take them 200,000 years before I would grant them fire. But in the next moment, they actually discovered how to make fire by friction. I was instantly furious. Don't snuff him out! My assistant gently blew, extinguishing their only flame. But even this couldn't quell my anger. I ordered my assistant to bring the elephant herd and drive the humans back into their damp, cold caves. This satisfied me a little, and I returned to my scientific research. Just then, a bold human stepped out of the cave. My rage erupted again. My assistant told me that humans were dancing to pray for rain. I realized I had forgotten to end the drought. I commanded my assistant to send them rain with a gentle spray. The human world was instantly drenched. Seeing their joyful faces, I felt a little proud. I ordered my assistant to continue spring, and the whole world came to life. But the next moment, I made a cruel decision. I decided that everything humans had must be granted by me personally to punish these rebellious humans. I ordered my assistant to release a plague on the human world, spraying poison. With my assistant's action, a plague instantly broke out in the human world. The entire tribe fell one after another, but even then I remained indifferent. Soon a few humans developed immunity, miraculously surviving. They realized something was wrong and began to kneel, praying to me, seeking forgiveness and dancing the dance of submission. Seeing this, I felt greatly satisfied, so I turned around and took a nap. When I woke up, two million years had passed in the human world. Those humans, once naked, starving, and only able to crawl on the ground to pray to me, now lived in modern high rise buildings. This almost made me faint with anger. To make them understand who their true master was, I pointed at the tallest building in the city, ordering my assistant to destroy it. My assistant lit a match, easily tossing it over. The building was instantly engulfed in flames, but it still didn't feel enough.

voice_to_text: Did you know there are currently 2,100 men on death row but only 48 women? Let's do another video where we talk about some of these women that are on death row and what exactly they did to get there. Really quickly before I begin, all three of the women I'm talking about today are from California. And death row in California has been dismantled. So that means that all three of these women are still serving a death sentence. However, they are no longer on death row and they're just in general population in prison. The first person I want to talk about today is 63 year old Cynthia Kaufman who has been serving a death sentence in California for the last 35 years. And she was actually the very first woman to receive the death penalty in California since it was reinstated back in 1977. She was sentenced to death after her and her boyfriend kidnapped and murdered four different women over the span of two months back in 1986. Cynthia began dating a man who had just been released from jail by the name of James Marlowe. Quickly after they began dating, they began using drugs, they got married and then they started to commit very violent crimes together. From October to November of 1986, they kidnapped and murdered four different women. On October 11th of 1986, they killed 32 year old Sandra Neary and on October 28th they killed 35 year old Pamela Simmons. Then on November 7th they Killed 20 year old Corina Novis and on November 12 they killed 19 year old Lionel Murray. They were both arrested just two days after killing Lynell. And when Cynthia was brought in for questioning, she immediately confessed to everything. At first she tried to tell police that James was abusing her and she was too scared to leave him and that she did not participate in the murders of the four women. But while she was in prison, she ended up confessing to her cellmate that she was absolutely in love with James and she did participate with all of the murders. In 1989 and 1990, Cynthia and James both went to trial where they were both found guilty of the murders of all four women and they were both sentenced to death. James is currently 68 years old and is serving his death sentence at the Richard J. Donovan Correctional Facility. Cynthia is currently 63 years old and is serving her death sentence at the Central California Women's Facility. And because she's in California, I don't think we will ever see her be executed. The next person on the list is 65 year old Carrie Dalton who has been serving a death sentence in California for the last 30 years. She was sentenced to death for the 1988 torture and murder of 23 year old Irene Melanie May. And still to this day Irene's body has never been found. On June 26 of 1988, Carrie and two other People, Cheryl Baker and Mark Tompkins were all together in a house with Irene. At some point, Carrie decided that Irene was a snitch and she eventually convinced both Mark and Cheryl that they all needed to kill her. Carrie decided that the best way to do this was to fill two syringes full of battery acid and then to inject Irene with those syringes. But when Irene wasn't immediately dying, they then began to be hit her over the head with a cast iron skillet and then they stabbed her several times. They then took her body and disposed of it. No one knows exactly how or what happened. And still to this day, her body has never been found. Both Mark and Cheryl cooperated with the detectives and told them everything that happened. And Mark Tomkins ended up pleading guilty to first degree murder and was sentenced to 25 years in prison. Cheryl Baker pled guilty to second degree murder and was sentenced to 15 years in prison. And I believe by now both of them have been released.

voice_to_text: This rooster keeps chain smoking because it knows it won't live much longer. To keep its owner from waking up and killing it, the rooster paints on the window to make the owner think it's still night time. It turns out that the morning before, when the rooster crowed, it saw the farmer sharpening an axe. At first, it thought this was just normal maintenance. But when it saw the farmer practicing chopping motions, it realised the danger. While the farmer went inside to rest, the rooster used its claws to drag the axe to the vegetable garden. Then it dug a hole and buried the axe, thought this would keep it safe. However, when the farmer watered the plants, the axe popped up from the soil. The farmer thought a new axe had grown in the ground, so he brought it back to the house. The desperate rooster spent all night thinking of solutions. The next day, while the owner was out, the rooster grabbed the axe to defend itself. But before it could act, it noticed a newspaper on the ground. That day was duck hunting season. Hunters would be out shooting ducks. The rooster came up with a crazy idea. It ran to the barn and stuck a toy duck on a hat as a gift for its owner. Once the farmer entered the cornfield, the rooster whistled loudly. Little did it know, this sounded like a duck call. As a result, it got all its feathers. Shut off. The rooster, then took a hand grenade, painted it white, pulled the pin, and placed it in the nest. The owner picked up this egg and shook it, thinking it would hatch into a chick. He had the rooster incubated. By the time the rooster tried to escape, it was too late. Soon, the owner approached with the axe. Rooster ran for its life and crashed headfirst into a tree. When it finally regained consciousness, it started writing its will. But surprisingly, the axe wasn't meant for it. The owner was chopping the tree behind it. The rooster breathed a sigh of relief. Just as it was celebrating with a dance, the tree fell right on its head. To help itself recover faster, the rooster started cooking itself. After drinking the chicken soup, it would be completely healed.

voice_to_text: What happened when you had to convince your own wife that she actually married you? Ava opened her eyes in the hospital bed after the car accident and smiled at me drowsily. But then she looked confused. Then fear overtook her. Why are you in my room? I reached for her hand, but she jerked away. Ava, I'm Silas, your husband. She shook her head violently. I'm not married. I'd remember being married. Held up my left hand, showing the ring she'd slipped on five years ago while crying happy tears. We've been together seven years, married for five. Her eyes went wide with panic. You're lying. This is insane. The doctors explained the amnesia while Ava stared at her own wedding ring like it might bite her. For three days I watched my wife treat me like a well meaning stranger. She was polite, but kept her distance. Her parents showed her our wedding album. You were so happy, her mother kept saying. Ava studied the photos clinically. She looks happy, she'd say. Like a bride with someone else entirely. At night, I'd go set up a planetarium. The place where we first fell in love. I arranged hundreds of photos and videos of her life before the accident, our life together. I truly believe that if she fell in love with me once, she could do it again. The drive to the planetarium felt like heading to my own execution. Ava sat pressed against the passenger door. Can You at least tell me why we're going to a planetarium, she asked. Because you once told me that you knew you'd marry me under these exact stars. She went quiet. That's either really romantic or really presumptuous. I couldn't tell if she was joking. Inside, I LED her to the center, where I recreated our first date exact, exactly. Same blankets, same spot, even the same brand of chocolate she'd brought to share. Sit here and look up, I said. Eva lowered herself carefully, still treating me like a stranger. Then the dome exploded with light. Her college graduation photo appeared first, spreading across the ceiling. That's me! She gasped. More photos bloomed like flowers around it. This is every moment that LED to us, I said. The photos changed to the bookstore where she'd worked.

voice_to_text: The man never expected that simply for looking down on his commoner status, the prince would kick him out of his team and even strip him of his position as a court mage. But what the prince didn't realize was that the man had been hiding his true strength all along. Back at the Magic Academy, he was known as the strongest defensive mage, not only mastering all the elemental magics, but also regarded as the most talented mage since the Academy's founding. After becoming a court mage, he focused on support magic to help the ambitious prince level up more efficiently. Yet the prince never noticed. He thought a commoner who only used support magic wasn't worthy of teaming up with him. Despite being expelled, the man didn't give up. After all, his own master had also been a court mage who was justly exiled. His goal was to challenge the kingdom's class system. The next day, he tried to meet with the king, explaining that the prince's team wasn't strong enough to tackle the 30th floor of the dungeon, which was extremely dangerous. But because of his commoner status, he couldn't even enter the castle gates. A mage from the prince's team came over to mock him, scoffing at the rumor that he had once broken the record for the 37th floor of the abyss to reach the 69th floor. To the mage, it sounded like nothing more than boastful nonsense. Unable to enter, the man tried to Hand his dungeon guide directly to the king. But the mage dismissed it, tearing the guide into pieces and ordering the guards to throw him out face. With such a humiliating outcome, he could only sign and prepare to leave the capital. Unexpectedly, he ran into a friend from his academy days. Red hair, upon hearing what had happened, immediately invited him to join his team. With nothing better to do, the man agreed. Together, they took a carriage to the dungeon city of Thistle, where the first step was registering him as an adventurer. Their target was the 52nd floor of the dungeon. But trouble came immediately. To enter floors above the 30th, one needed a special task only available to guild members with at least two and a half years of membership. Red hair was frustrated. There was no way to wait that long. Complaining would do no good. We suggested exploring the lower floors first. The man agreed it was a good chance to warm up. Having spent every day in the princess team casting support magic, he finally had a chance to show his offensive power. The two worked seamlessly, and the monsters in the shallow floors were no match. But oddly, instead of speeding through, the number of monsters kept increasing. Sensing something wrong, the man prepared to unleash his long, unused defensive magic. Red hair cooperated, casting a defensive barrier to protect the area. The man's lightning spell struck instantly, wiping out all the Red flying insects on the map. Just as he thought the battle was over, a giant abissal worm burst from underground and bit red hair. The man immediately understood the anomaly on this floor was caused by this creature. Were such a giant monster he was in his element. The massive worm was instantly killed by his sacrificial heavy strike, while red hair, as the Academy's top support mage, had long since cast a protective barrier around himself. The man's spell reminded him of their Academy days when they reached the 68th floor of the dungeon and were completely helpless against the boss, only to have him arrive late and instantly obliterated with a full element magic spell. Now that he had returned to the team, their combined strength meant they could break records once again.
